.TH PROCTOP 1 "March 11, 2026" "proctop 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
proctop \- small terminal process monitor for Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B proctop
[\fB--log\fR \fIfile\fR] [\fIfilter\fR]
.br
.B proctop
\fB--help\fR
.br
.B proctop
\fB--version\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B proctop
reads system and process information from
.I /proc
and displays CPU usage, per-core CPU usage, memory usage, uptime, load average,
GPU information when available, and a live process table.
.PP
If a
.I filter
string is provided, only processes whose displayed command contains that
substring are shown.
.PP
Tree mode may be toggled inside the UI. Search mode may be started inside the
UI and applies the same command substring filter logic used by the startup
argument.
.SH CONTROLS
.TP
.B q
Quit.
.TP
.B Esc
Quit, or cancel search mode.
.TP
.B r
Refresh immediately.
.TP
.B m
Sort by memory usage.
.TP
.B p
Sort by process id.
.TP
.B c
Sort by CPU usage.
.TP
.B t
Toggle process tree mode.
.TP
.B /
Start interactive search mode.
.TP
.B Up / Down
Move the selected process row.
.TP
.B K
Start SIGTERM confirmation for the selected process.
.TP
.B X
Start SIGKILL confirmation for the selected process.
.TP
.B Y / N
Confirm or cancel an active terminate/kill prompt.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --help
Show help text and exit.
.TP
.B --version
Show version information and exit.
.TP
.B --log
Append visible process snapshots to the given text file.
.SH AUTHOR
Written for the proctop project.
